EXTRACTED VALUE: Jansen is regarded as a tough-tackling but talented ball-player, and at 6ft 3in represents an aerial threat both at set-pieces and crosses.
Quresma has enjoyed a terrific season for Porto but speculation remains that he will soon be on his way to one of the continent's heavyweight clubs.
In 2006, he was the youngest player in Spanish football history to represent the country in a World Cup.
While his international career has been something of a rollercoaster, his club experiences have been shrouded in controversy.
But still he has been a regular inclusion for Marco van Basten and he will provide cover for the front-line in Austria & Switzerland.
He made seven appearances in the qualification campaign and is likely to be given a key role in Austria and Switzerland.
